2
00:00:52,511 --> 00:00:55,305
Today, we'll be learning about
the Trolley Dilemma.

3
00:00:57,099 --> 00:00:58,558
Who knows what a "trolley" is?

4
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:01,061
-What is that?
-Trolley?

5
00:01:01,144 --> 00:01:02,396
-Beats me.
-What is it?

6
00:01:04,690 --> 00:01:07,693
It's a streetcar. Do you recognize it now?

7
00:01:07,776 --> 00:01:10,195
-I've seen that on TV.
-I see.

8
00:01:10,279 --> 00:01:11,488
I saw it in a movie.

9
00:01:11,572 --> 00:01:14,950
This trolley's brakes are broken,

10
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:18,662
and there are five workers
working on the track.

11
00:01:19,413 --> 00:01:22,416
<i><font color="white">If you do nothing about it,
all five of them will die.</font></i>

12
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:25,335
But if you pull a lever,

13
00:01:25,419 --> 00:01:28,922
you can change the trolley's course

14
00:01:29,006 --> 00:01:30,549
to a different track.

15
00:01:31,174 --> 00:01:32,175
However,

16
00:01:32,843 --> 00:01:36,346
there's another worker working
on that track as well.

17
00:01:37,639 --> 00:01:39,224
Let's think about this.

18
00:01:39,308 --> 00:01:40,851
If you don't do anything,

19
00:01:40,934 --> 00:01:43,770
<i><font color="white">the trolley will kill five people.</font></i>

20
00:01:43,854 --> 00:01:47,816
<i><font color="white">If you pull the lever
to change its direction,</font></i>

21
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:50,068
<i><font color="white">the five workers will survive</font></i>

22
00:01:50,152 --> 00:01:52,404
<i><font color="white">but that one worker will die.</font></i>

23
00:01:55,991 --> 00:01:57,492
What will be your decision?

24
00:01:58,535 --> 00:02:00,704
I'll definitely pull the lever.

25
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:02,205
I'm not sure.

26
00:02:02,289 --> 00:02:03,123
Yes?

27
00:02:03,206 --> 00:02:06,668
I would definitely switch the tracks.
It's five to one.

28
00:02:06,752 --> 00:02:10,130
But those five were fated to die.

29
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:13,216
If I pull the lever, that one worker

30
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:15,302
would suddenly meet their death.

31
00:02:15,886 --> 00:02:17,220
That would haunt me forever.

32
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:19,681
This is giving me a headache.

33
00:02:19,765 --> 00:02:21,391
Do we have to decide?

34
00:02:22,017 --> 00:02:23,352
Then who will?

35
00:02:23,435 --> 00:02:24,770
Not me.

36
00:02:25,395 --> 00:02:26,980
Hey, you can decide.

37
00:02:27,064 --> 00:02:29,441
No. Why should I?

38
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:31,735
There's no right answer to this dilemma.

39
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:33,695
We each have an opinion.

40
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:37,824
All right. Write a paper
about what you would do and why.

41
00:02:37,908 --> 00:02:40,494
