Come on, Mom.

674
00:47:38,939 --> 00:47:40,274
Don't be like that.

675
00:47:40,357 --> 00:47:42,318
Didn't you miss me? It's been three years.

676
00:47:43,360 --> 00:47:45,821
Why would I miss the daughter
who abandoned me?

677
00:48:20,648 --> 00:48:21,899
Honey.

678
00:48:25,569 --> 00:48:26,445
Hye-joo.

679
00:48:38,707 --> 00:48:40,251
This is just too hard.

680
00:48:49,802 --> 00:48:51,053
Someone died…

681
00:48:55,307 --> 00:48:56,642
because of me.

682
00:49:05,401 --> 00:49:06,360
No.

683
00:49:07,278 --> 00:49:08,904
It wasn't your fault.

684
00:49:08,988 --> 00:49:12,366
You didn't do anything wrong.
You're not to blame, honey.

685
00:49:13,492 --> 00:49:15,786
You didn't know this would happen.

686
00:49:17,413 --> 00:49:18,455
But…

687
00:49:22,084 --> 00:49:24,378
But they lost their son

688
00:49:25,629 --> 00:49:26,839
because of me.

689
00:49:32,178 --> 00:49:35,472
<i><font color="white">Ever since I fell in love with him,</font></i>

690
00:49:37,141 --> 00:49:38,100
<i><font color="white">I…</font></i>

691
00:49:39,476 --> 00:49:41,270
I know exactly how that feels.

692
00:49:42,479 --> 00:49:46,442
<i><font color="white">…have never once doubted…</font></i>

693
00:49:46,525 --> 00:49:47,526
It's all my fault.

694
00:49:48,319 --> 00:49:49,570
<i><font color="white">…the kind heart he has…</font></i>

695
00:49:50,487 --> 00:49:51,947
They lost their son.

696
00:49:53,949 --> 00:49:55,534
<i><font color="white">…toward this world</font></i>

697
00:49:56,619 --> 00:49:58,329
<i><font color="white">-that we lived in.</font></i>
-I'm here.

698
00:49:58,412 --> 00:49:59,830
-Have some of this.
-<i><font color="white">Not once.</font></i>

699
00:50:00,998 --> 00:50:02,124
Hey.

700
00:50:02,208 --> 00:50:03,042
Come sit.

701
00:50:03,542 --> 00:50:04,418
Come on.

702
00:50:11,300 --> 00:50:12,676
Stay a bit longer.

703
00:50:13,385 --> 00:50:16,305
-We can eat together.
-That's okay.

704
00:50:16,388 --> 00:50:18,849
You should save it for tomorrow.

705
00:50:18,933 --> 00:50:20,517
Don't worry about tomorrow.

706
00:50:21,185 --> 00:50:22,019
I'll be back.

707
00:50:22,811 --> 00:50:24,563
Enjoy your meal. Goodbye.

708
00:50:24,647 --> 00:50:26,023
-Are you sure?
-Yes.

709
00:50:26,106 --> 00:50:27,274
-Come by again.
-I will.

710
00:50:32,655 --> 00:50:34,490
-Goodbye.
-Go home safely.

711
00:50:34,573 --> 00:50:35,532
-Okay.
-Go on.

712
00:50:38,369 --> 00:50:40,663
Goodbye. Go home safely.

713
00:50:40,746 --> 00:50:41,997
-Okay.
-Bye.

714
00:50:42,998 --> 00:50:45,834
HAJEONG-DONG, SINYANG-GU

715
00:50:47,836 --> 00:50:49,922
She must work at the community center.

716
00:50:50,005 --> 00:50:51,048
No.

717
00:50:51,548 --> 00:50:54,009
I asked her and she said she didn't.

718
00:50:56,428 --> 00:50:57,471
Then where?

719
00:50:58,013 --> 00:51:00,015
I'm not sure. I don't even know her name.

720
00:51:00,599 --> 00:51:01,892
She won't tell me.

721
00:51:02,476 --> 00:51:05,229
But you haven't told me
where you're from either, young man.

722
00:51:07,773 --> 00:51:08,816
I'm not that young.

723
00:51:08,899 --> 00:51:10,818
Goodness. Are you married?

724
00:51:10,901 --> 00:51:13,112
You look so young.

725
00:51:13,195 --> 00:51:14,238
I have a child.

726
00:51:15,197 --> 00:51:17,908
-A child?
-Ma'am, the stew is getting cold.

727
00:51:17,992 --> 00:51:19,493
-Let's eat.
-Okay.

728
00:51:48,814 --> 00:51:50,566
It's been three years now.

729
00:51:51,108 --> 00:51:52,735
Who could it be?

730
00:51:52,818 --> 00:51:54,862
They sent us a hefty sum.

731
00:51:54,945 --> 00:51:55,821
Exactly.

732
00:51:55,904 --> 00:51:59,533
-And it's anonymous, so they'll be taxed.
-Did the Anonymous Angel come by again?

733
00:51:59,616 --> 00:52:03,370
Yes. Along with a million won,
just like the other times.

734
00:52:03,454 --> 00:52:04,913
Let me help.

735
00:52:04,997 --> 00:52:06,457
-Let's put it on the cart.
-Okay.

736
00:52:06,957 --> 00:52:08,083
-One, two…
-One, two…

737
00:52:14,631 --> 00:52:17,593
I fixed it,
so it should last you a bit longer.

738
00:52:17,676 --> 00:52:20,888
Goodness, thank you.
You're better than my own kids.

739
00:52:29,855 --> 00:52:31,357
-I'll get going.
-Hold on.

740
00:52:33,233 --> 00:52:34,276
Here.

741
00:52:34,360 --> 00:52:36,195
-Thank you.
-Go on.

742
00:52:36,278 --> 00:52:37,363
Goodbye.

743
00:52:43,869 --> 00:52:45,746
Goodness. You're here.

744
00:52:45,829 --> 00:52:47,456
Hello. Have you been well?

745
00:52:48,040 --> 00:52:49,291
Have some apples.

746
00:52:49,375 --> 00:52:50,626
Okay.

747
00:53:37,798 --> 00:53:39,633
SINYANG-GU SENIOR WELFARE CENTER

748
00:54:01,155 --> 00:54:02,156
Ma'am.

749
00:54:02,656 --> 00:54:03,782
Ma'am, the meat--

750
00:54:11,790 --> 00:54:13,250
You're here.

751
00:54:14,001 --> 00:54:15,461
-Hello.
-Goodness.

752
00:54:26,722 --> 00:54:28,390
-Eat up.
-Okay.

753
00:54:30,225 --> 00:54:31,226
Thank you.

754
00:54:32,394 --> 00:54:34,813
I'll get you some rice tea.

755
00:54:34,897 --> 00:54:35,814
Let me.

756
00:54:35,898 --> 00:54:39,485
It's okay. You two stay and eat.
I'll go get it.

757
00:54:39,568 --> 00:54:40,736
Sit down.

758
00:54:40,819 --> 00:54:41,695
Come on.

759
00:55:02,716 --> 00:55:04,927
About that rice…

760
00:55:06,595 --> 00:55:09,723
I didn't tell anyone, so don't worry.

761
00:55:11,433 --> 00:55:12,392
Thank you.

762
00:55:25,656 --> 00:55:28,784
My name is Nam Joong-do.

763
00:55:28,867 --> 00:55:29,826
What's your name?

764
00:55:29,910 --> 00:55:31,119
I'm Hye-joo.

765
00:55:32,329 --> 00:55:33,497
Kim Hye-joo.

766
00:55:35,290 --> 00:55:36,667
Ms. Kim Hye-joo.

767
00:55:38,126 --> 00:55:38,961
How pretty.

768
00:55:41,838 --> 00:55:45,050
I meant your name. You have a pretty name.

769
00:56:22,379 --> 00:56:23,297
My child died

770
00:56:24,715 --> 00:56:26,341
because of you.

771
00:56:30,262 --> 00:56:31,221
Get out!

772
00:56:31,805 --> 00:56:33,348
How dare you come here?

773
00:56:33,932 --> 00:56:35,267
Get out of here this instant!

774
00:56:35,350 --> 00:56:36,268
Get out!

775
00:56:37,477 --> 00:56:39,771
How dare you set foot in here?

776
00:56:45,527 --> 00:56:48,363
Mom, I'm hungry. Let's eat.

777
00:56:48,447 --> 00:56:51,116
-I don't want to.
-We haven't eaten together in a while.

778
00:56:51,199 --> 00:56:53,952
Why are you being so friendly? Let me go.

779
00:56:54,036 --> 00:56:56,872
-Mom.
-Did you forget that you left me?

780
00:57:20,437 --> 00:57:21,480
Will you have the baby?

781
00:57:24,900 --> 00:57:27,361
I'm not sure. Would you prefer that?

782
00:57:30,155 --> 00:57:32,783
I guess that depends on who the father is.

783
00:57:35,535 --> 00:57:37,245
Ji-hoon might not be the father.

784
00:57:42,918 --> 00:57:43,961
You're right.

785
00:57:44,962 --> 00:57:46,630
He might not be.

786
00:58:04,314 --> 00:58:11,071
I LOVE YOU, MOM AND DAD.
SINCERELY, NAM JI-HOON

787
00:58:32,300 --> 00:58:34,845
TROLLEY

788
00:58:34,928 --> 00:58:38,724
You know that I gave you up
to share with the world, right?

789
00:58:38,807 --> 00:58:40,267
I just want to be here with you.

790
00:58:40,350 --> 00:58:43,145
<i><font color="white">I came by to see you,
so I'll just be doing that.</font></i>

791
00:58:43,228 --> 00:58:44,771
<i><font color="white">Are you going to stay in that house?</font></i>

792
00:58:44,855 --> 00:58:46,398
Then lay low, as if you're dead.

793
00:58:46,481 --> 00:58:47,899
<i><font color="white">Don't get too attached to her.</font></i>

794
00:58:47,983 --> 00:58:49,443
<i><font color="white">I'm afraid you'll get hurt.</font></i>

795
00:58:49,526 --> 00:58:50,569
<i><font color="white">I got tested for drugs.</font></i>

796
00:58:50,652 --> 00:58:53,655
I don't know what to feel
whenever I see her.

797
00:58:53,739 --> 00:58:56,533
<i><font color="white">Frankly, I'm very disappointed
in your wife.</font></i>

798
00:58:56,616 --> 00:58:58,285
Youngsan? Why all of a sudden?

799
00:58:58,368 --> 00:59:00,954
<i><font color="white">It's your hometown,
so I was wondering if you knew anyone.</font></i>

800
00:59:01,538 --> 00:59:02,873
<i><font color="white">If you had to choose</font></i>

801
00:59:02,956 --> 00:59:05,959
between the world you dream of
and your wife,

802
00:59:06,043 --> 00:59:07,794
<i><font color="white">which one would you choose?</font></i>

803
00:59:08,420 --> 00:59:13,300
Subtitle translation by: Soo-ji Kim

